direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Tell us!  What is it like outside? The squeeze toys rush Buzz like JABBERING excited children. EXT. CRANE GAME With the kids gone, Woody crosses the aisle to the crane game and dives through the prize slot. INT. CRANE GAME - CONTINUOUS Woody clambers up the side of the deposit slot.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: This is an intergalactic emergency! I need to commandeer your vessel to Sector 12! Woody peeks over the partition to witness Buzz surround by the cute alien toys.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued; to the aliens) Who's in charge here? All the aliens point upward.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: The cla-a-a-a-a-a-a-a-w!! Woody and Buzz look up. ANGLE: CRANE GAME CLAW It dangles directly above the toys.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: The claw is our master.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: The claw chooses who will go and who will stay.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (to himself) This is ludicrous.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (laughter) Woody GASPS at the recognition of Sid's voice.  He turns to see Sid heading straight for the crane game.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, no!  Sid!!! Woody leaps off the partition and tackles Buzz, pushing the two of them deep into the pile of aliens.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Get down!! Sid approaches the crane game and fishes quarters out of his pants pocket.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (loud whisper) What's gotten into you, Sheriff?  I was -- WOODY (loud whisper)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: are the one that decided to climb into this -- ALIEN #4 (loud whisper) Sh-h-h-h-h-h.  The claw.  It moves. ANGLE: CLAW It moves into position and hovers directly above the area where Woody and Buzz are hiding. The crane drops and grabs hold of the alien toy that is right on top of Buzz.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (whispering excitedly) I have been chosen!! Positioned with his back to Sid, the alien is lifted up by the claw.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued) Farewell, my friends!  I go on to a better place.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Gotcha! With the alien gone, Buzz's upper torso becomes exposed, forcing the space ranger to freeze.  Sid suddenly spots Buzz.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Buzz Lightyear!  No way! Woody, still hidden, frantically looks around for some way to escape.  Behind him, through the aliens, he eyes... A SMALL REPAIR DOOR Woody swims through the alien squeeze toys toward the door. He grabs hold of the locking latch and, after a few attempts, is able to pry the door open. The shadow of the crane lines up over Buzz, lowers, and grabs his head.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Yes! The claw begins to lift Buzz up.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Buzz, NO! Woody grabs hold of Buzz's feet. Woody and the claw begin to have a tug-of-war with Buzz. Woody pulls down hard, forcing Buzz to sink into the pile of aliens, out of Sid's view.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (slamming his fist against the glass) Wha -- ?  Hey!! Still tugging against the crane, Woody is almost out the door with Buzz.  Just then, the aliens at the bottom of the pile pull Buzz and Woody back inside.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He has been chosen.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey!  What are you doing?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He must go.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Stop it, you -- !  Stop it, you zealots!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He must go!  Do not fight the claw! Do not anger the claw!  He has been chosen. Woody and Buzz are pushed up to the surface and into the air, dangling lifelessly in front of Sid.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Alright!  Double prizes! Woody and Buzz are dropped into the prize door slot and snatched up by Sid.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (looking at his two new toys) Let's go home and...play.  Ha-ha-ha. ANGLE: CLOSEUP OF SKULL ON SID'S T-SHIRT MATCH DISSOLVE TO: EXT. SID'S HOUSE - LATER THAT NIGHT From out of the darkness appears Sid on his skateboard.  He is HUMMING to rock music from his walkman while carrying his backpack in his hand. Sid leaps off the skateboard and walks up the front path towards the front door. Through the open zipper, Buzz peeks out of the backpack to see Sid's house.  He recognizes Andy's house next door. INT. BACKPACK - CONTINUOUS Buzz, Woody and a squeeze toy alien are scrunched up in the backpack.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Sheriff!  I can see your dwelling from here!  You're almost home.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Nirvana is coming!  The mystic portal awaits!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (to Alien) Will you be quiet?!! (to both) You guys don't get it, do you? Once we go into Sid's house, we won't be coming out. ANGLE: TOYS' POV FROM OUT BACKPACK The front door opens to reveal Scud.  The dog lunges straight for the backpack, BARKING.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Whoa, Scud!  Hey, boy.  Sit!  Good boy! The dog begrudgingly obeys.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey, I got somethin' for ya, boy. Sid's hand reaches into the backpack.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (loud whisper)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: !!! The toys go still.  Sid's hand grabs the alien out of the backpack.  The alien is then placed sideways along Scud's snout.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Ready, set, NOW. In one quick motion, Scud flips the alien up, catches it in his mouth, and rabidly shakes it back and forth. Buzz and Woody react in horror.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hannah!  Hey, Hannah!!! Woody and Buzz glance up to see HANNAH, Sid's frail little sister, carrying her Janie Doll.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Did I get my package in the mail?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I dunno.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Whaddaya mean, you don't know?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (insistent) I don't know!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (mock concern) Oh no, Hannah!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Look!  Janie! He grabs the doll.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey!!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: She's sick!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (panic rising) No she's NOT -- SID I'll have to perform one of my...operations!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: ... Don't touch her!  NO! Sid bolts upstairs with Hannah in pursuit.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Not Sid's room...not there... INT. UPSTAIRS HALL - CONTINUOUS Sid races to his bedroom door.  Hannah is right behind.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Sid!  Give her back! Sid just LAUGHS.  He charges into the room and slams the door in his sister's face. INT. SID'S ROOM - CONTINUOUS HANNAH (O.S.) (pounding on his door) Sid!  Sid!... Sid carelessly tosses the backpack on the bed and walks over to a makeshift workbench.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (as Doctor) Oh, no.  We have a sick patient here, nurse.  Prepare the O.R., STAT! Sid CLICKS on a bare bulb dangling above his "operating table." Woody and Buzz look on from the safety of the backpack as Sid places the Janie doll's head in a vise.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Sid, give her back!  Give her back now!  I'm telling!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (as Doctor) Patient is... (straining while tightening vise) ...pre-e-epped. Sid grabs a painter's mask from his toolchest and dons it like a surgeon's mask.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (as Doctor) No one's ever attempted a double bypass brain transplant before. Sid grabs a toy pterodactyl from a nearby crate full of junk.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (as Doctor) Now for the tricky part -- pliers!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (whispering to Woody) I don't believe that man's ever been to medical school. Sid struggles for a moment with his "patient" then stops.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (as Nurse) Doctor, you've done it! (running to the door) Hannah? He opens the door.  Hannah is standing there, looking worried.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued) Janie's all better now. He hands her Janie -- her head has been replaced with a pterodactyl's.  Hannah SCREAMS at the sight of the monstrosity and bolts down the hallway.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: !!  MOM!!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: She's lying!  Whatever she says it's not true! Sid throws the doll to the ground and runs after Hannah, slamming the door behind him. Woody and Buzz peer out of the backpack at their new surroundings.  Heavy metal posters, discarded toy remains and power tools adorn the messy room. They are in Hell...toy Hell.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We are gonna die. (bolting out of the pack) I'm outta here! Woody leaps from the bed to the doorknob and struggles to open it.  No good.  Woody drops to the floor.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Locked!  There's gotta be another way out of here. SFX: ROLLING SOUND Woody is startled by the noise. A small yo-yo rolls out from behind a box and falls on its side. Spooked, Woody grabs a pencil from the floor and brandishes it like a weapon. Just then a shadow passes by Woody.  He turns quickly but sees nothing.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Uh...Buzz?  Was that you? Woody hurriedly trades his pencil for a larger flashlight. He hears a NOISE from under Sid's bed.  Woody turns on the flashlight and shines the beam in the direction of the noise, illuminating... A BABY DOLL HEAD'S PROFILE WOODY Hey!  Hi, there, little fellah! Come out here.  Do you know a way out of here? The baby doll moves out from under the bed, revealing a one- eyed doll head atop a spider-like body made of erector set pieces.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (GASP!!) The creature extends its legs and rises up taller than Woody. Scared speechless, Woody keeps his flashlight beam locked on BABYFACE. Various other MUTANT TOYS begin to emerge from the shadows: a toy fishing pole with fashion doll legs, a skateboard with a combat soldier's torso screwed to the front end, a jack- in-the-box with a rubber hand for a head, (and others). Woody leaps onto the bed and hides behind Buzz.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: B-B-B-Buzz! Buzz and Woody look on as the mutants have a tug of war as they grab all the Janie and pterodactyl parts, dragging them off into the shadows.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: They're cannibals! Woody retreats back into the backpack. INT. BACKPACK - CONTINUOUS Woody cowers in the corner as Buzz enters.  He punches a button on his chest.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: May day!  May day!  Come in, Star Command!  Send reinforcements!... (pause) Star Command, do you copy? No response. Buzz adjusts his laser light.  It emits a short BLIP.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (aiming his arm out the pack) I've set my laser from stun to kill.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, great, great.  Yeah, and if anyone attacks us we can blink 'em to death. EXT. ANDY'S HOUSE - NIGHT Rex points a flashlight out of Andy's bedroom window while Bo Peep, Slinky, Hamm and Potato Head look on. Some bushes rustle below.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey, you guys!  I think I've found him.  Buzz!  Is that you?! Rex points the flashlight beam at the shaking bushes.  The annoyed MEOW of a cat is heard.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Whiskers!  Will you get out of here?!  You're interfering with the search and rescue. SFX: APPROACHING CAR Rex turns off the flashlight.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (whispering) Look!  They're home! The toys duck behind the sill. The Davis' family van pulls into the driveway.  Andy and Mrs. Davis get out.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Mom, have you seen Woody?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Where was the last place you left him?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (searching the van) Right here in the van.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, I'm sure he's there.  You're just not looking hard enough.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He's not here, Mom.  Woody's gone. The toys all look at one another.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Woody's gone?!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Well waddah-ya-know, the weasel ran away. Hamm, Potato Head and Rex walk away from the window.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Huh?!  Huh?!  I told you he was guilty.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Who would've thought he was capable of such atrocities?! Bo Peep and Slinky are left alone at the window, visibly crestfallen.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, Slink, I hope he's okay.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (as Interrogator) Oh, a survivor.  Where is the rebel base?  Talk! SFX: HAND SLAP INT. SID'S ROOM - CONTINUOUS An inanimate Woody flies across the room, landing hard on the floor. Sid crosses to the window.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (as Interrogator) I can see your will is strong. Sid opens the window shade.  Bright sunlight shines down onto Woody.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued) Well, we have ways of making you talk. Sid pulls out a magnifying glass from his back pocket and focuses the beam on Woody's forehead.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (as Interrogator) Where are your rebel friends now? Heh, heh. A bright white hot dot forms on Woody's forehead and begins to smolder.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Sid!!  Your pop-tarts are ready! Sid pulls the magnifying glass away.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Alright!! Sid runs out of the room.  As soon as he's gone, Woody jumps up SCREAMING, his forehead burning. He runs to a bowl of half-eaten cereal (with milk) on the floor, and dunks his head in. Buzz runs over to Woody, pausing to remove two suction cup darts from his person before pulling Woody out of the bowl. Two colorful Froot-Loops stick to each of Woody's eyes like glasses.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Are you alright? (whacking him on the back) I'm proud of you, Sheriff.  A lesser man would have talked under such torture. Woody looks at his reflection in the back of the cereal spoon and rubs the burn mark on his forehead.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I sure hope this isn't permanent.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (checking his wrist communicator) Still no word from Star Command. We're not that far from the spaceport -- Woody's eyes light up. ANGLE: SPOON Sid's bedroom door can be seen in the reflection.  It's open.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: The door!  It's open!  We're free!! Woody runs for the door.  Buzz follows.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Woody, we don't know what's out there!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I'll tell you what's -- AAAAH! THE MUTANT TOYS suddenly appear and block their path to the doorway.  Woody hides behind Buzz.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: They're gonna eat us, Buzz!!  Do something!  Quick!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Shield your eyes! Buzz fires his laser at them.  The little red beam just flickers against Babyface's head.  The mutant toys look confusedly at each other.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It's not working.  I recharged it before I left.  It should be good for hours -- WOODY Oh, you idiot!  You're a toy!  Use your karate chop action! Grabbing Buzz like a hostage, Woody fends off the mutant toys by pushing a large button on Buzz's back, making Buzz's arm involuntarily "chop" up and down.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (to mutants) Get away!  Hoo-cha!  Hoo-cha!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey!!  Hey!  How are you doing that? Stop that!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Back!  Back, you savages!  Back! Woody circles around the mutant toys to the open doorway, continually chopping Buzz's arm.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Woody, stop it!!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Sorry guys, but dinner's canceled! Woody drops Buzz and runs out the door. INT. UPSTAIRS HALLWAY - CONTINUOUS Woody races down the corridor...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (to himself) There's no place like home. There's no place like home. There's no place like home... ...turns onto the top of the stairwell, down a few steps, and is confronted by... SCUD asleep on the landing. Woody freezes inches away from the sleeping beast.  He slowly backs up the stairs. Suddenly Buzz appears and pulls Woody back against the hallway wall.  He covers Woody's mouth with his hand.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (muffled gasp)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (whisper) Another stunt like that, cowboy -- you're going to get us killed.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (pulling Buzz's hand away) Don't tell me what to do!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Shhh! Buzz checks to make sure Scud is still asleep and then darts across the stairwell opening to the other end of the hallway. Once safely across, he motions for Woody to follow. Woody cowardly crawls on all fours across the open area and meets up with Buzz. As he stands... WOODY'S PULLSTRING RING gets caught on one of the curls of the wrought iron railing. The toys begin to creep down the hallway, unaware that Woody's pullstring is being pulled farther and farther until -- It SNAPS off the iron railing and flies back towards Woody.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: YEEEEEEE-HAAAAAAA!! Both Buzz and Woody leap in surprise at the sound of Woody's voice box. ANGLE: SCUD'S EYE It opens. Woody vainly attempts to stifle the recoiling pullstring.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued) Giddy-up partner!... GROWLING, Scud starts up the stairs.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued) ...We got to get this wagon train a movin'! Woody and Buzz take off running.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Split up! Two doors are ajar at the other end of the hallway.  Buzz dives behind one while Woody jumps into... A CLOSET Woody slams the door shut just as Scud reaches the top of the landing.  CRASHED can be heard from behind the closet door, getting Scud's attention. Buzz peeks out from his doorway at Scud SNIFFING AND GROWLING at the closet. Sensing movement behind him, Scud whips around and starts to enter Buzz's doorway. SFX: SNORING The noise stops the dog in his tracks.  Both Scud and Buzz look up to see... INT. SID'S DAD'S DEN - CONTINUOUS MR. PHILLIPS is asleep on a La-Z-Boy recliner in front of the T.V. Scud backs out and heads down the stairs. Buzz turns to exit the room when he hears...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Calling Buzz Lightyear!!  Come in Buzz Lightyear!!  This is Star Command.  Buzz Lightyear!  Do you read me?!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Star Command! Buzz opens up his wrist communicator and is just about to speak into it when he is interrupted.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Buzz Lightyear responding!  Read you loud and clear! Buzz turns around to see... A TELEVISION SET Buzz's space ranger logo is on the screen over a field of stars.  The image quickly changes to two young boys playing in their backyard with a Buzz Lightyear doll.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Buzz Lightyear, Planet Earth needs your help!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (into toy wrist communicator) On the way!
direction.name: direction

dialogue.raw_text: : EXT. SID'S BEDROOM WINDOW - DAY SID (O.S.)
dialogue.name: dialogue

direction.raw_text: !!! Buzz reacts with confusion at what he is watching.  He walks slowly towards the television set.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: The world's greatest superhero! Now the world's greatest TOY! ANGLE: TV COMMERCIAL The Buzz Lightyear doll is now out of the box and being displayed.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Buzz has it all!  Locking wrist communicator!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Calling Buzz Lightyear.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Karate chop action!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Wow! With every feature demonstrated on the TV, Buzz compares the same feature on himself.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Pulsating laserlight!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Total annihilation!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Multi-phrase voice simulator!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It's a secret mission in uncharted space! Buzz presses the same button on his uniform.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It's a secret mission in uncharted space!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: And best of all... (big "monster truck" voice)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: To Infinity and Beyond! On the TV screen, the Buzz Lightyear action figure appears to be launched through the air.  The words:  NOT A FLYING TOY flash across the bottom of the screen.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (non-excited lawyer voice) Not a flying toy. Buzz slowly shakes his head in wide-eyed disbelief.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Get your Buzz Lightyear action figure and save a galaxy near you!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: !!! The image on the screen changes to a shot of hundreds of Buzzes in their boxes lining either side of a store aisle.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Available at all Al's Toy Barn outlets in the tri-county area. Buzz is stricken.  He looks down at his wrist communicator and opens it. ANGLE: WRIST COMMUNICATOR Molded on the underside of the cover are three words: "MADE IN TAIWAN." SONG: "I WILL GO SAILING NO MORE" BEGINS INT. UPSTAIRS HALLWAY - CONTINUOUS Buzz walks dejectedly out of the den and down the hallway. As he passes the top of the stairwell he pauses to look up through the railing at... A SMALL WINDOW It is open, revealing the blue sky beyond.  A bird flies past. The taunting voice of Woody echoes in his head.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You are a toy!  You can't fly! Buzz bows his head, defeated. BEAT Slowly Buzz raises his head, determination in his eyes.  He slams the offending wrist communicator shut, as if to deny its message of "Made in Taiwan." Buzz climbs up the railing to the banister.  He pops open his wings, and aims himself towards the window above.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: To Infinity and Beyond! Buzz leaps off the banister... and falls. In SLOW MOTION Buzz watches his square of blue sky pull farther away from him as he plummets to the floor below. INT. SID'S HOUSE/ENTRYWAY - CONTINUOUS Buzz CRASHES on the entryway floor. Buzz opens his eyes to see... HIS SEVERED LEFT ARM The broken arm lies a few inches away from his now empty arm socket. Buzz drops his head back in defeat. SONG ENDS HANNAH (O.S.) M-o-o-om?  Mom, have you seen my Sally doll? Hannah walks into the entryway, and not seeing Buzz, steps on him.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What, dear?  What was that? Hannah picks up Buzz (and his arm) and smiles.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Nevermind.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oo-o-of! (to the hallway) Buzz?!  The coast is clear.  Buzz? Where are you?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It's a secret mission in uncharted space!  Let's go!! Woody creeps down the hallway, dragging the Christmas lights with him.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Really?  That is so-o-o interesting. Woody peeks into the open doorway of... INT. HANNAH'S BEDROOM/UPSTAIRS HALLWAY - CONTINUOUS Hannah is pretending to have a tea party.  Her guests are dolls, headless dolls, that is except for... BUZZ He is seated at the miniature table, dressed up in a frilly apron and fashionable party hat.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued) Would you like some tea, Mrs. Nesbit?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (under his breath) Buzz! Hannah has placed a tiny teapot in Buzz's severed arm and pours imaginary tea with it.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It's so nice you could join us on such late notice. Woody steps back into the hallway.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, no!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What a lovely hat, Mrs. Nesbit.  It goes quite well with your head. Woody thinks for a moment, then takes a few steps further down the hall.  He CLEARS HIS THROAT.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (high voice) Hannah!  Oh, Hannah! Hannah stops pouring tea and looks up.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (yelling out her room) Mom? (to the dolls) Please excuse me, ladies.  I'll be right back. As soon as Hannah exits the room Buzz keels over face-down onto the table. Hannah passes Woody, hidden in the Christmas lights, and walks downstairs.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What is it, Mom?  Mom, where are you? Woody bolts into Hannah's room.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Buzz!  Hey, Buzz!  Are you okay? Buzz lifts his head up and wails in drunken despair.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Gone!  It's all go-o-one!  All of it's gone.  Bye-bye!  Whoo-hoo! See ya! Woody picks up Buzz's severed arm.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What happened to you?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: One minute you're defending the whole galaxy... (pointing at other dolls) ...and suddenly you find yourself suckin' down Darjeeling with Marie Antoinette and her little sisters. The headless dolls turn and wave. Woody removes the teapot from the severed arm and sets it on the table.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I think you've had enough tea for today. (helping Buzz up) Let's get you out of here, Buzz.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (grabbing Woody) Don't you get it?!  You see the hat? I am Mrs. Nesbit!! (hysterical laughter)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Snap out of it, Buzz! Woody presses Buzz's helmet open, slaps him across the face with his own detached arm, and then politely closes the helmet. Buzz sobers up and calmly takes his severed arm from Woody. Buzz walks out of the room while Woody follows.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (sober) I'm sorry.  You're right. INT. UPSTAIRS HALLWAY - CONTINUOUS BUZZ (continued) ...I'm just a little depressed, that's all.  I can get through this. Buzz reaches the center of the hallway and drops to his knees.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, I'm a sham!!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (loud whisper) Sh-h-h-h-h!!  Quiet, Buzz.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Look at me!  I can't even fly out of a window! Woody stops short.  He looks down the hallway in the direction of Sid's room. ANGLE: SID'S BEDROOM WINDOW Woody can see straight out Sid's window across the way to Andy's bedroom window.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued) But -- the hat looked good.  Tell me the hat looked good!  The apron is a bit much, it's not my color...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Out the window...Buzz, you're a genius! Woody grabs the coil of Christmas lights and drags Buzz towards Sid's room.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued) Come on, this way!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Years of Academy training...wasted!! EXT. ANDY'S HOUSE/ANDY'S BEDROOM WINDOW Mr. Potato Head and Hamm are playing Battleship.  Hamm's wearing Potato Head's hat.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Miss.  G-6.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Ohhh!  You sunk it!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Heh-heh.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Are you peeking?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, quit your whining and pay up. Potato Head reaches for his ear.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No, no, not the ear.  Gimme the nose.  C'mon!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (pulling out his nose; nasally) How 'bout three out of five? He is about to hand his nose over to Hamm when...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey guys!  Guys!  Hey! Both toys look across the way. EXT. SID'S WINDOW/ANDY'S BEDROOM WINDOW - CONTINUOUS Woody has just finished lifting Sid's window and waves to the toys.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Son of a building block, it's Woody!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He's in the psycho's bedroom!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hi!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (into Andy's bedroom) Everyone, it's Woody! INT. ANDY'S BEDROOM - CONTINUOUS Slinky, Bo Peep and Rex look to the window.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Woody?!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You're kidding?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Woody?! INT. SID'S ROOM WOODY We're gonna get outta here, Buzz -- Buzz? Buzz is not there.  Woody looks down at the floor. Buzz is sitting on the floor, playing "bombs away" with his broken arm. EXT. ANDY'S BEDROOM WINDOW/SID'S WINDOW The rest of Andy's toys gather around the window to see Woody.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey, look!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Woody!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Boy, am I glad to see you guys!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I knew you'd come back, Woody!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What are you doing over there?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It's a long story, Bo.  I'll explain later.  Here, catch this! Woody tosses one end of the Christmas lights over.  Slinky catches them.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I got it, Woody!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (overly excited) He got it, Woody!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Good going, Slink!  Now, just, just tie it on to something!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Wait!  Wait!  I got a better idea! How about we DON'T?! Potato Head grabs the string of lights away from Slinky.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey?!!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Potato Head!?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Did you all take stupid pills this morning?!  Have you forgotten what he did to Buzz?  And now you want to let him back over here?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No, no, no!  You got it all wrong, Potato Head.  Buzz is fine!  Buzz is right here.  He's with me!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You are a liar!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No, I'm not! (to Buzz) Buzz, come over here and you just tell the nice toys that you're not dead. ANGLE: BUZZ He doesn't respond, preoccupied with peeling off the sticker on his wrist communicator.  He crumples it up and tosses it aside.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (to Andy's toys) Just a sec. INT. SID'S ROOM - CONTINUOUS Frantic, Woody walks over to the edge of the desk.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Buzz!  Will you get up here and give me a hand?! Buzz's severed arm comes flying into view and lands by Woody's feet.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (insincerely) Ha ha.  That's very funny, Buzz. (exploding) This is serious!!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey, Woody!?  Where'd ya go?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He's lyin'.  Buzz ain't there. EXT. SID'S WINDOW/ANDY'S WINDOW Woody reappears at the edge of Sid's window.  He pretends to notice something out of the other toy's view.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (forced casualness) Oh, hi Buzz!  Why don't you say "hello" to the guys over there? BUZZ'S SEVERED ARM suddenly appears with Woody holding the end just out of sight.  Woody throws his voice, pretending to be Buzz.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hi ya, fellas.  To infinity and beyond!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey look!  It's Buzz!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (shaking the arm's hand) Yeah, hey Buzz.  Let's show the guys our new secret best-friends hand shake.  Gimme five, man!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Something's screwy here.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: So, you see?  We're friends now, guys.  Aren't we, Buzz? (as BUZZ) You bet.  Gimme a hug. Woody makes Buzz's arm grab his neck and pull him forward.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued; as himself) Ha, ha, oh, I love you, too.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: See?  It is Buzz.  Now give back the lights, Potato Head.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Wait just a minute.  What are you trying to pull?!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Nothing. Woody innocently shrugs and throws both his hands up... ...exposing the severed arm. The toys all SCREAM in horror.  Rex clasps his hands to his mouth and turns away to BARF. Realizing his mistake, Woody tries to hide the arm, but it's too late.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, that is disgusting.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Murderer!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No!  No, no, no, no!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You murdering dog!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No, it's not what you think, I swear!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Save it for the jury.  I hope Sid pulls your voice-box out, ya creep! Potato Head drops the lights.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No!  No!  Don't leave!  Don't leave! You've gotta help us, please!  You don't know what it's like over here!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (to the other toys) Come on.  Let's get out of here.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Go back to your lives, citizens. Show's over. All the toys leave the window except Slinky.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Come back!  Slink!  Slink, please! Please!  Listen to me! Unable to look Woody in the eye, Slinky closes the blinds.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued) No!  No!  Come back!  SLI-I-I-INKYYY!! SFX: THUNDER As storm clouds roll over Sid's house, Woody slumps over the window sill in defeat. INT. SID'S ROOM - CONTINUOUS BROKEN TOY SOUNDS emit from behind Woody.  He turns from the window to see... THE MUTANT TOYS converging all around Buzz.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: !! Still holding onto Buzz's arm, Woody jumps down from the desk and runs to Buzz's rescue.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Go away, you disgusting freaks! Babyface turns from the fray and charges at Woody with his erector-set pinchers. Woody cowers, shielding himself from Buzz's arm. Babyface clamps onto the arm and has a tug-o-war with Woody.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Alright back!  Back, you cannibals! Woody loses his grip on the arm and sails across the room, crashing into the wall. By now there is no sight of Buzz within the swarming mass of mutant toys. Woody attacks the mob with a vengeance.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He is still alive, and you're not gonna get him, you monsters! He furiously throws the mutant toys aside, digging his way to... BUZZ He is sitting up, his broken arm now newly-attached. Woody's anger turns to confusion.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey?!  Hey, they fixed you! Woody shakes Buzz's arm to confirm what he's seeing is real when he looks to the mutants.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued) But -- but they're cannibals.  We saw them eat those other toys. The mutant toys part to reveal the recent victims of Sid's last "operation": The Janie Doll and Pterodactyl.  Their heads have been taped back on the correct bodies. The mutants all innocently stare at Woody.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Uh...sorry.  I...I thought that you were gonna... (laughs nervously) ...you know, eat my friend. Immediately, the mutant toys retreat back into the dark corners of the room.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey!  No, no, wait!  Hey!  What's wrong?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Sid!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Not now, Mom, I'm BUSY!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Sid!!! FOOTSTEPS approach the bedroom.  Woody tries to pick up the still depressed Buzz, but he just goes limp.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Buzz!  C'mon, get up!  Buzz, you're... (GRUNT) ...get up... Woody begins dragging Buzz towards the bed, but their progress is too slow.  He shakes Buzz hard.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Fine.  Let Sid trash you.  But don't blame me. Woody leaves Buzz sitting alone in the middle of the floor and hides underneath a nearby milkcrate just as... Sid enters carrying a big box.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It came!  It finally came! Sid runs over to his workbench and rips open the box.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (reverently) The big one. He pulls out a rocket with "THE BIG ONE" written on it.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (reading the rocket label) "Extremely dangerous.  Keep out of reach of children."  COOL... (looks around) What am I gonna blow?  Man...hey, where's that wimpy cowboy doll? Sid spots the milkcrate and picks it up. No Woody. ANGLE: UNDERSIDE OF MILKCRATE Out of Sid's view, Woody presses against the inside, hanging on for dear life. SFX: BUZZ'S LASER Sid looks down and notices he's stepping on Buzz, activating his laser.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Yes!  I've always wanted to put a spaceman into orbit.  Ha-ha. He places Buzz and the milkcrate on the workbench and throws a toolbox on top of the crate. The impact of the toolbox dislodges Woody from his hiding place.  Woody quickly ducks under a magazine on the floor of the crate "jail." Woody watches helplessly as Sid fishes out a roll of electrical tape from the toolbox and, with an IRREVERENT CHUCKLE, tapes Buzz to the rocket. SFX: THUNDERCLAP A flash of lightning interrupts the moment.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, no... Sid crosses to the window to see a huge rainstorm commence. Sullenly, he smacks his head against the window.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Aw, man...! Woody heaves a SIGH of relief. Suddenly Sid's face brightens.  He turns his focus from the rain to the Buzzrocket.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (as Newscaster) Sid Phillips reporting.  Launch of the shuttle has been delayed due to adverse weather conditions at the launch site.  Tomorrow's forecast... Sid smacks Buzz down on the desk, winds his alarm clock, and places it next to Buzz.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Sunny.  Ha-ha-ha.  Sweet dreams. INT. ANDY'S BEDROOM - THAT NIGHT Andy is being tucked into bed by his mother.  She hands him his cowboy hat.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I looked everywhere, honey, but all I could find was your hat.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (groggy) But what if we leave them behind?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, don't worry, honey, I'm sure we'll find Woody and Buzz before we leave tomorrow. Andy's eyes shut.  Mom turns out the light and quietly exits the room. A moving box on the floor, with the words "Andy's Toys!" scrawled on it, begins to shake from side to side.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (muffled) Aaaah!  I need air! Rex pops out of the top of the box, COUGHING a packing styrofoam peanut out of his mouth.  Potato Head appears beside him.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (relieved) Aa-a-a-a-ah! (COUGH)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Will you quit moving around?!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I'm sorry.  It's just that I get so nervous before I travel.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: How did I get stuck with YOU as a moving buddy? Potato Head drops back down into the box.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (following Potato Head) Everyone else was picked. BO PEEP peeks around the corner of one of the boxes and looks up at Andy fast asleep clutching his cowboy hat.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, Woody, if only you could see how much Andy misses you. EXT. SID'S HOUSE - LATER THAT NIGHT THUNDER RUMBLES as rain pours down outside the spooky dwelling. INT. SID'S ROOM Sid is in bed fast asleep. Woody struggles to move his milkcrate jail, but with the weight of the toolbox on top it won't budge. Woody looks across the desktop at Buzz sitting dejectedly with the rocket strapped to his back.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Ps-s-s-s-t!  Psst!  Hey, Buzz! No reaction from Buzz. Woody picks up a stray washer from the desktop and flings it at Buzz, striking his helmet. Buzz lifts his head and turns lifelessly to look at Woody.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hey!  Get over here and see if you can get this tool box off me. Buzz just looks away from Woody and bows his head.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, come on, Buzz.  I...Buzz, I can't do this without you.  I need your help.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I can't help.  I can't help anyone.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Why, sure you can, Buzz.  You can get me out of here and then I'll get that rocket off you, and we'll make a break for Andy's house.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Andy's house.  Sid's house.  What's the difference.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, Buzz, you've had a big fall. You must not be thinking clearly.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No, Woody, for the first time I am thinking clearly. (looking at himself) You were right all along.  I'm not a Space Ranger.  I'm just a toy.  A stupid little insignificant toy.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Whoa, hey -- wait a minute.  Being a toy is a lot better than being a Space Ranger.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Yeah, right.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No, it is.  Look, over in that house is a kid who thinks you are the greatest, and it's not because you're a Space Ranger, pal, it's because you're a TOY!  You are HIS toy.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: But why would Andy want me?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Why would Andy want you?!  Look at you!  You're a Buzz Lightyear.  Any other toy would give up his moving parts just to be you.  You've got wings, you glow in the dark, you talk, your helmet does that -- that whoosh thing -- you are a COOL toy. Woody pauses and looks at himself.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (continued; depressed) As a matter of fact you're too cool. I mean -- I mean what chance does a toy like me have against a Buzz Lightyear action figure?  All I can do is... Woody pulls his own pull-string.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: There's a snake in my boots! Woody bows his head.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Why would Andy ever want to play with me, when he's got you? (pause) I'm the one that should be strapped to that rocket. Woody slumps dejectedly against the crate, his back to Buzz. Buzz lifts up his foot. ANGLE: THE SOLE OF BUZZ'S FOOT The signature "ANDY" reads through the dirt and scuff marks. Buzz gazes back at Woody.  A look of determination spreads across his face.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Listen Buzz, forget about me.  You should get out of here while you can. Silence. Woody turns around. Buzz is gone. Suddenly, the entire milkcrate begins to shake.  Woody looks up to see... BUZZ He is on top of the milkcrate, trying to push the tool box off.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Buzz!!  What are you doing?  I thought you were -- BUZZ Come on, Sheriff.  There's a kid over in that house who needs us. Now let's get you out of this thing.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Yes Sir! Both Buzz and Woody push the milkcrate and together, they finally get it to move but it's slow progress.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (strained) Come on, Buzz!  We can do it! SFX: TRUCK The two toys stop to look out the window by the workbench. ANGLE: OUT SID'S BEDROOM WINDOW With the rain stopped and the sun beginning to rise... A MOVING TRUCK can be seen pulling up in front of Andy's house.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Woody!  It's the moving van.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We've got to get out of here...NOW. Buzz braces himself between the tool chest and the wall. Using his legs, Buzz pushes with all his might.  The toolbox begins to move. Woody notices that with every shove Buzz gives to the tool chest, the milkcrate begins to edge out over the lip of the desk.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: C'mon, Buzz. Finally the gap is wide enough for Woody to jump through. Woody drops down to the floor below.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (loud whisper) Alright.  Buzz!  Hey!  I'm out! Buzz doesn't hear Woody and continues to shove the toolbox (and milkcrate) farther out.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: ...almost (GRUNT) ...there (GRUNT) ... Woody looks up just in time to see the entire toolbox and milkcrate topple towards him.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (nervous laugh) The toolbox CRASHES right on top of Woody. Buzz falls onto the desktop and glances over to Sid, who stirs...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (in his sleep) I wanna ride the pony... Sid does not wake.  Buzz heaves a SIGH OF RELIEF, then peers over the edge of the workbench.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Woody!  Woody?!  Are you alright?! Woody lifts himself out from under the rubble.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (punch-drunk) No, I'm fine...I'm okay... SFX: ALARM CLOCK It goes off by Sid's bed.  Woody drops back under the toolbox and Buzz goes limp. Sid groggily sits up for a beat, then his eyes light up.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, yeah!  Time for lift-off! Sid jumps out of bed, grabs Buzz and bolts out of the room.
direction.name: direction

result.heading: "I WILL GO SAILING NO MORE" BEGINS INT

dialogue.raw_text: : INT. UPSTAIRS HALLWAY - LATER ANGLE: CLOSET The knob jiggles for a moment.  Suddenly, the door flies open revealing Woody, entangled in Christmas lights, standing atop a pile of boxes to be at doorknob height. Woody and the rest of the junk topple over. A bowling ball topples out, smashing Woody square on the head.
dialogue.name: dialogue

direction.raw_text: !! Woody leaps to his feet, runs across the room, and catches the door just before it closes.  As he swings the door back open Woody is confronted by... SCUD The dog barrels down the hallway straight for Woody.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Aaah!  Back!  Back!  Down!  Down! Woody slams the door shut just in time.  Scud BARKS AND SCRATCHES at the door.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (out of breath; to himself) Okay, what do I do?  Come on Woody, think! Woody looks across the room. THE MUTANT TOYS have appeared all around the room.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Guys! The mutant toys all scatter and hide.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No, no, no!  Wait!  Wait!  Listen! Please!  There's a good toy down there and he's -- he's going to be blown to bits in a few minutes all because of me.  I've gotta save him! (pause)
direction.name: direction
